|WKO=====================================================================
|YKOCyberware is machinery grafted into your own body. An installed
implant grants its bonuses - stats, resistances, or chance-based "proc"
effects - for as long as it stays inside you.

Every implant occupies one or more body locations: eyes, ears, brain,
skull, jaw, throat, neck, spine, heart, lungs, torso, skin, shoulders,
arms, hands, legs, and feet. Only one implant may occupy a location.

Implants also strain the body. Your strain limit starts at 6 and grows
with your level: +1 per 10 levels, plus larger bonuses at levels 50,
100, 150, 200, and 250. Souls remorted through cyber-touched origins
gain +2 strain each, to a maximum of +10. You cannot install an implant
that would push your total strain past your limit, and an implant may
demand a minimum level or stranger things before your body accepts it.

|WKBCommands:|YKO
  |YKBcyberware            |YKOShow installed technological implants, occupied
                       body locations, and cybernetic strain.
  |YKBimplants             |YKOShow every object-backed implant by family,
                       including cyberware and bound relics.
  |YKBcyberscan <implant>  |YKOInspect an implant's type, grade, locations,
                       strain, visibility, and procs before installing.
                       Street Samurai receive additional contract details for
                       signature hardware. Their own installed implants also
                       show integrity, fragmentation, firmware effectiveness,
                       software issues, and recommended maintenance actions.
  |YKBinstall <implant>    |YKOInstall an implant you are carrying.
  |YKBextract <implant or location>  |YKORemove an installed implant,
                       returning it to your inventory. Alias: |YKBuninstall|YKO.

Installation and extraction require a staffed ripperdoc clinic, and the
ripperdoc will not operate while you are fighting. The Forbidden Replacement
Table in Nethrys Undercity's Ripperdoc Quarter is a formal clinic. You may use
|YKBengage ripperdoc|YKO there to review carried or installed hardware, see
the exact service fee, and confirm a procedure. You may use |YKBcyberware|YKO
and |YKBcyberscan|YKO anywhere.

Street Samurai diagnostics are private. A carried signature implant shows its
contract requirements and hardware profile, but live maintenance state appears
only when that exact implant is installed in the scanning Street Samurai.
Ordinary implants and scans by other players retain the standard report.

Installation costs 10,000 coins per point of implant strain, with a 10,000
coin minimum. Extraction costs 5,000 coins per strain, with a 5,000 coin
minimum.

Installed implants cannot be dropped and stay with you across sessions.
Relics and other non-technological implants can occupy the same anatomical
slots, but do not consume strain unless their own rules say otherwise.
Some implants are outwardly visible - anyone who looks at you will see
them - while hidden ones stay your secret. Procs trigger on their own
in combat: on your hits, when you take damage, when you are badly hurt,
or when you make a kill, each with its own chance and cooldown.

